  "meta": {
    "display_name": "BJJ TOKYO",
    "tagline": "QUIET. FAST.",
    "subtitle": "MU × BJJ TOKYO — competition jiu-jitsu, stripped to the essentials.",
    "h1": "Nothing wasted.",
    "accent_hex": "#0a4d9c",
    "lede": "Jiu-jitsu is subtraction, not addition. Drop the wasted motion, cut the noise, finish on the shortest path. BJJ TOKYO carries MU's philosophy — quiet, fast — into competition jiu-jitsu. Built from MU's minimal vocabulary (無 nothing · 月 moon · 円相 the zen circle · 柔 the gentle art · 帯 the belt) in monochrome plus a single jiu-jitsu blue. The global face of the line — same drop, English-first.",
    "hero_kv": [
      [
        "Category",
        "Competition BJJ apparel"
      ],
      [
        "First drop",
        "16 SKU (scaling to 100)"
      ],
      [
        "Base / Domain",
        "Tokyo / bjj.sh"
      ],
      [
        "Design",
        "MU — 無 / 月 / 円相 / 柔 / 帯"
      ],
      [
        "Accent",
        "Jiu-jitsu blue #0a4d9c — a nod to the blue belt"
      ]
    ],
    "why_md": "Most jiu-jitsu apparel is loud. BJJ TOKYO goes the other way.<br>無 (cut the waste), 月 (the MU lineage), 円相 (the one-stroke zen circle that completes in a single move), 柔 (softness overcomes hardness), 帯 (the proof of rank) — only the signs that matter, in monochrome plus one jiu-jitsu blue.<br>Wears as a daily training kit, a competition travel uniform, or an academy's own merch. Zero-inventory print-on-demand, so a gym or academy can run it under its own name.",
    "use_cases": [
      "Daily training & open mat",
      "Competition travel team kit",
      "Academy & gym merch (zero inventory risk)",
      "Cross-academy exchange gifts",
      "Belt promotion & podium keepsakes",
      "Spectator & support goods (sticker / bandana / tote)"
    ]
  },
